threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, missing section headers at jd

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated downloader/dropper that employs fileless execution and process masquerading. It initiates a connection to a hardcoded C2 server (23.226.135.117) on port 3879, downloads an XOR-encrypted (key 0x99) payload, and writes it into an anonymous memory-backed file descriptor (using memfd_create via syscall 0x13f). The downloaded code is then executed using fexecve under the deceptive process name '[kworker/0:2]' to mimic a legitimate kernel thread. It also utilizes /tmp/log_de.log as a mutex to prevent multiple infections.
